# Architecture Rules

This repository produces a publishable npm module.

## Required layers

- Rust/WASM is the core crypto engine for performance-critical and correctness-critical code.
- JavaScript is the public API layer for npm consumers.
- README and package docs are required parts of the product, not optional extras.
- Tests must cover both Rust correctness and JavaScript-facing integration behavior.

## Responsibilities

- Keep heavy crypto and complex scalar / group operations in Rust.
- Keep initialization, environment handling, validation, wrappers, and package ergonomics in JavaScript.
- Do not expose raw WASM glue as the primary user-facing API unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve the layered design: engine in Rust, consumer surface in JS.

## Porting policy

- The Rust implementation is based on a known working C++11 repository.
- Preserve semantic equivalence with the C++11 reference unless explicitly instructed otherwise.
- Correctness and parity come before refactoring elegance.

## Package mindset

- Every change should be evaluated as part of a real npm library.
- Prefer stable, explicit, well-documented exports.
- Avoid leaking Rust internals into the JS-facing package API.